- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with cross-lingual word embeddings and bilingual lexicon induction, which are both related to natural language processing.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a method based on a Gaussian mixture model and normalizing flow, which are both machine learning techniques.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with a task that requires intelligence and understanding of language.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the use of word embeddings in image captioning and visual question answering tasks.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also less likely but possible as the paper mentions the use of neural networks in the proposed method.
